Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro alleges plan against him             Sigomba Ramadhan Omar  10th Sep 2019 11:21:25 GMT +0300 Sigomba Ramadhan Omar  10th Sep 2019 11:21:25 GMT +0300 Sigomba Ramadhan Omar   Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro at a past event. The legislator has alleged that there are plans to harm him. (Standard)    Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro at a past event. The legislator has alleged that there are plans to harm him. (Standard) Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro at a past event. The legislator has alleged that there are plans to harm him. (Standard) Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro at a past event. The legislator has alleged that there are plans to harm him. (Standard) Besieged Kiharu Member of Parliament Ndindi Nyoro now claims that there are plans to hurt him and he is afraid that his life is in danger.   "I am only pleading with them. Please let no one think of harming me because I know there are those plans," said Ndindi Nyoro while appearing in court in Murang'a.  The lawmaker alleges that a police officer who happens to be his friend disclosed to him that he was supposed to be taken from Murang'a Police Station to Kamukunji Police Station in Nairobi.  "We know this and I can substantiate. Where I was supposed to be taken, there were two people found with capital offense. I was supposed to be taken there and it was not in good faith," claimed Nyoro.  SEE ALSO :Murang'a college closed 30 years ago in to be reopened SEE ALSO : Murang'a college closed 30 years ago in to be reopened     Speaking to journalists at Murangá Law Courts on Tuesday 10, the Kiharu MP pleaded with Interior Permanent Secretary Karanja Kibicho not to involve police officers in politics.  "I want to tell our PS Kibicho, please let's not involve our police officers in politics. I listened to you yesterday very professional and I know they (Police) are people who respect the law so let's not misuse them," said Ndindi.  The embattled Member of Parliament yesterday claimed that he has been receiving threats for supporting William Ruto and the 'Tangatanga' movement. Tangatanga' Tangatanga' movement.  For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.     Nyoro also said that there is no need for sending GSU officers to arrest him because he will surrender to the police whenever he is summoned.  "I am obedient and whenever they want me I want to request, don't even send those GSU officers, I will surrender," Said Ndindi.  SEE ALSO :Catholic bishop bans politicians from church events SEE ALSO : Catholic bishop bans politicians from church events The lawmaker also said that he is terrified and he could not speak further as he waited to be charged with assaulting a police officer and resisting arrest during a fracas at Gitui Catholic Church on Sunday which involved nominated MP Maina Kamanda.  We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Ndindi Nyoro Kiharu Mp William Ruto Tangatanga Movement